        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 1:26AM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 126 AM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Draketown, or near
Buchanan, moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind and heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Atlanta, Marietta, Douglasville, Dallas, Buchanan, City of South
Fulton, Smyrna, East Point, Villa Rica, College Park, Powder Springs,
Austell, Bremen, Temple, Hiram, Waco, Lithia Springs, Fair Oaks,
Vinings, and Brownsville.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. Motorists should
slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 200 AM EDT for northwestern
Georgia.</instruction>
